
[1]avarice

   AV'ARICE, n. [L. avaritia, from avarus, from aveo, to covet.]

   An inordinate desire of gaining and possessing wealth; covetousness;
   greediness or insatiable desire of gain.

   Avarice sheds a blasting influence over the finest affections and
   sweetest comforts of mankind.
